[DhtmlXQ_comment10]Black pushes the pawn foward to target and slow the development of the red horses.||Although this would slow the development of the other chess pieces, the red horses would need some time be be developed. Give and take, it would still be an acceptable alternative.[/DhtmlXQ_comment10]
[DhtmlXQ_comment14]Black plays the side cannon first to announce his intentions of preparing to capture the red cannon, thereby forcing it to be fixed in position. Once the cannon's position is fixed, red's formation would be thus disrupted and the poor development of the right red horse would become more apparent.[/DhtmlXQ_comment14]
[DhtmlXQ_comment18]It would seem that black would lose a one move initiative with this move but it would add increased pressure on red's right horse.||If red were allowed to push P3+1 to exchange pawns, red have an easy time in the game to come.[/DhtmlXQ_comment18]
